I"A<ol>
  <li>Add potatoes into a large pot and cover with salted water. Boil the potatoes. Reduce heat to medium-low and simmer until tender, about 20 minutes. Drain and set aside to cool slightly.</li>
  <li>Heat olive oil in a pan at medium heat and cook onion with garlic for 5 minutes.</li>
  <li>Bring a small saucepan of water to a boil. Boil pepper until soft, about 5 minutes. Run pepper under cold water to cool until cool enough to handle; remove and discard skins and veins.</li>
  <li>Bring another small saucepan of water to a boil. Boil carrot until soft, about 5 minutes</li>
  <li>Blend onions, pepper, cheese, salt, pepper, carrot, 1/2 cup of evaporated milk and half of a packet of soda crackers (5 crackers) in a blender until smooth.</li>
  <li>Add the rest of evaporated milk and soda crackers into the blended mixture while continuing to blend until a creamy sauce is achieved.</li>
  <li>Serve potatoes and pour huancaina on the top of it.</li>
  <li>Arrange 1 lettuce leaf onto each plate and top it with an egg half and two black olive halves (optional).</li>
</ol>
